gametext: At same location, Resistance characters and [Resistance] starships are each defense value and forfeit +1. While at an [Episode VII] location with a Resistance leader, adds one battle destiny.
lore: \b Leader.\b0
name: Admiral U.O. Statura

gametext: While aboard a starship, it is power and defense value +2 and immune to Lateral Damage. May 'fly' (landspeed = 2). Permanent weapon is Electroshock Prod (may target a character of ability < 4; target may not use its game text for remainder of turn).
lore: \b Information broker\b0  and \b spy\b0 .
name: C1-10P (Chopper)

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Droid starfighters are power and forfeit -1 here. During battle, may add or subtract 1 from a just drawn even destiny.
lore: Clone trooper commander.
name: CC-2237 (Odd Ball)

gametext: During battle, target opponent's starfighter with your snub fighter. Starfighter's gametext (except related to any capacity and the ability and identity of any permanent pilot) is canceled. OR If your pilot of ability < 3 was just lost from aboard a snub fighter, take pilot into hand.
lore: First perfected by Corellian starship battle tacticians, this dangerous counter-maneuver has saved numerous hot-shot pilots in life-or-death situations.
name: Corellian Slip (V)

gametext: Once per game, may deploy 2-1B here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per turn, if present at a site, may 'operate' on your Disarmed character (or your just 'hit' non-droid character of ability < 4) present here; character is restored to normal.
lore: Veteran of Battle of Hoth. Medic and \b scout\b0  assigned to General Solo's assault force. Prides himself on being an efficient soldier in General Madine's commando organization.
name: Corporal Delevar (V)

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While piloting an X-wing alone, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise and all immunity to attrition here is canceled. Once during your control phase, may take Sabotage into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Abednedo.
name: Ello Asty

gametext: While a Skywalker here, Prophecy Of The Force may not relocate from here.\par No starships or vehicles here.
light_side_text: While a Skywalker here, Prophecy Of The Force may not relocate from here.
name: Endor: Ewok Village (V)

gametext: Deploys -1 to a war room. While at a war room, your capital sharships at Rebel Base systems may not be targeted by weapons and your Rebels and T-47s at same and related Rebel Base locations move for free to same or related locations.
lore: One of the original founders of the Rebel Alliance. Former civilian strategist with the House of Organa. Somber \b leader\b0  of Echo Base.
name: General Carlist Rieekan (V)

gametext: \ul Deploy Jedi Council Chamber (with Prophecy Of the Force there), Ewok Village, and I Feel The Conflict.\ul0 \par \b For\b0  remainder of game, you may not deploy [Episode I] Jedi (except Yoda) or [Episode I] padawans. Luke may not be captured by Bring Him Before Me unless there are 2 or more cards stacked on Insignigicant Rebellion during any move phase. \par \b While\b0  this side up, you may initiate battles for free. \par \b Flip\b0  this card if Luke (or a Jedi) at a battleground site and opponent has no characters or ability > 4 at battleground sites.\par \b While\b0  this side up, once during your control phase, may peek at up to X cards from the top of your Reserve Deck, where X = number of battlegrounds you occupy; take one into hand and shuffle your Reserve Deck. During your draw phase, may retrieve any one card; opponent may stack a card from hand on I Feel The Conflict to place that card out of play instead.\par \b Flip\b0  this card (unless Vader crossed over) if opponent's character of ability > 4 at a battleground site or you do not have Luke (or a Jedi) at a battleground site.
name: He Is The Chosen One/He Will Bring Balance

gametext: Take one security droid into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR During your control phase, if K-2SO controls opponent's site, opponent loses 1 Force. OR If a battle was just iniated where K-2SO is with your spy, lose K-2SO to cancel that battle. OR Cancel Nevar Yalnal.
lore: Unlike the Empire, the Alliance treats their droids with respect. Many droids volunteered to share the risk of battle and aid the Rebellion's assault on the Death Star.
name: I've Got A Bad Feeling About...

gametext: When deployed, may take a non-unique Resistance character into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While present on Jakku, if opponent just Force drained at an adjacent site, they retrieve no Force with Graveyard Of Giants.
lore: Abednedo \b scavenger\b0 .
name: Ilco Munica

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. If armed with a blaster or rifle at a site (or piloting Red 5), may add one destiny to total power or attrition. Run Luke, Run! is a Used Interrupt. Immune to attrition < 4.
name: Luke Skywalker, The Rebellion's Hope

gametext: Deploy on non-Jedi Luke. May target a character for free. Target loses any immunity to attrition for remainder of turn. Draw destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if destiny + 2 > defense value. If about to be lost, may lose 1 Force to place on bottom of Used Pile.
lore: Merr-Sonn Model 57. Part of an arms lot purchased for the Alliance from a black market dealer on Ord Mantell. Carried by Luke as backup for his father's lightsaber.
name: Luke's Blaster Pistol (V)

gametext: Resistance characters here may not have their forfeit reduced. If you just forfeited a 'hit' non-droid character from same or related site, may lose 1 Force to place that character in Used Pile.
lore: Female.
name: Major Harter Kalonia

gametext: Cancel the game text of Jodo or any Fett for remainder of turn. OR Take Sabine, Under Attack, or a blaster into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR During a battle, if opponent just drew more than two battle destiny, cancel one of those destiny draws (your choice).
lore: Most space-faring adventurers meet their fate with a calm, quiet dignity.
name: Mandalorian Mishap (V)

gametext: May add 2 pilots and 2 passengers. May deploy (with a pilot) or move as a 'react' to same system as a Rebel starship. When with \ul Ghost\ul0 , adds one destiny to total power.
lore: Phoenix Squadron.
name: Phantom

gametext: Deploy on a site. While at a battleground, adds one [Dark Side Force] icon and one [Light Side Force] icon here. Once per turn, if a player just Force drained at a site with total ability > 5, relocate this Effect to that site. Once per game, may retrieve a card with "Anakin" in title into hand. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The turning of Vader and the loss of Palpatine was the beginning of a new era for the entire galaxy.
name: Prophecy Of The Force

gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Once per game, may deploy Jawa Ion Gun (for free) on R'kik from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. When defending a battle at Dune Sea or a desert, and all your ability here is provided by Jawas, opponent may not draw battle destiny here.
lore: A tribe of Tusken Raiders, a herd of angry banthas, a raging Krayt Dragon and R'kik. Minutes later, the Jawa emerged from the Dune Sea, a bantha tusk over his shoulder.
name: R'kik D'nec, Hero Of The Dune Sea (V)

gametext: May add 1 pilot. While Ello Asty piloting, attrition against opponent is +1 here.
name: Red Squadron 6

gametext: If Yavin 4 on table, deploy on table. If you just initiated a Force drain at a battleground system (except a 'liberated' system), may draw destiny. Add 1 for each piloted unique (*) snub fighter present at that system. If total destiny > 5, opponent loses 1 Force and stacks that card face down there (while that card stacked there, system is 'liberated'). If opponent Force drains at a 'liberated' system, place stacked card in owner's Used Pile. At each 'liberated' system, your Force drains are +1 and opponent's starships are deploy +1.
name: Restore Freedom To The Galaxy

gametext: \ul Once per turn, if drawn for destiny, you may activate 1 Force.\ul0  During battle at a site, choose: Your total power is +1 for each of your characters present. OR If you have a weapon present, opponent must use or lose 1 Force to draw their first battle destiny.
lore: Echo Base heavy weapons units provided covering fire, allowing Alliance personnel to escape Hoth.
name: Suppressive Fire (V)

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Imperials and bounty hunters deploy +1 here. Once per game, if a battle droid was just lost from same location, may steal it into hand.
name: Temmin "Snap" Wexley

gametext: Cancel Too Cold For Speeders. OR Unless opponent's AT-AT or AT-ST at a battleground site, retrieve 1 Force for each Rebel Base location you control (limit 3). OR Your Rebels and T-47s at sites where opponent has an AT-AT or AT-ST are power +2 for remainder of turn.
lore: "Echo station, 3TA. We have spotted Imperial walkers." A Rebel tactic is to put as much ground as possible between walkers and Rebel troops, allowing time to prepare a defense.
name: Walker Sighting (V)

gametext: Deploy on table. May deploy Lor San Tekka from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per turn, if you just lost a Resistance character from a Jakku site, may take a Resistance character of lesser ability into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
name: Why Does Everyone Want To Go Back To Jakku?!

gametext: Deploy on table. While you have fewer than 13 cards in hand, non-unique aliens are immune to Monnok. Opponent may not increase deploy cost of your aliens. Once per turn, may deploy Arleil, Doallyn, Tessek, \ul Wild Karrde\ul0 , or a Tatooine battleground from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Female dancer from Askajia. Very protective mother. Makes sure that all those she cares about are well protected.
name: Yarna d'al' Gargan (V)

gametext: \ul Deploy Yavin 4 system and Massassi War Room. May deploy Restore Freedom To The Galaxy.\ul0 \par \b While\b0  this side up, once per turn, may use 1 Force to deploy a battleground system from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. \par \b Flip\b0  this card if Rebels control two battleground systems (or if four Rebels are on table).\par \b While\b0  this side up, during battle at sites related to systems you occupy, for each piloted unique (*) snub fighter present at that system, your total power is +2. Once during your draw phase, if a system is 'liberated,' may place a card from your Lost Pile out of play to retrieve 1 Force.\par \b Flip\b0  this card if you do not occupy two battlegrounds (unless four Rebels are on table).
name: Yavin 4 Base Operations/The Time To Fight Is Now

dark_side_text: Opponent's characters here are immune to Set For Stun.
gametext: Once per game, may deploy a Rebel leader here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.\par Opponent's characters here are immune to Set For Stun.
light_side_text: Once per game, may deploy a Rebel leader here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Yavin 4: Massassi War Room (V)

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. \ul If drawn for weapon or battle destiny, may take into hand to cancel and redraw that destiny.\ul0  Power +1 for each Dark Jedi here. During your control phase, unless a Dark Jedi at a battleground, may retrieve 1 Force. Immune to attrition < 6.
lore: "I've taken care of everything."
name: Young Skywalker

gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. During battle with an opponent's combat vehicle (or with two Rebels), attrition against opponent is +2. Rebels here are immune to Trample.
lore: Lasat.
name: Zeb Orrelios

gametext: Deploy on table. During your deploy phase, you may reveal one Star Destroyer from hand to take its matching pilot character from Reserve Deck (or vice versa) and deploy both simultaneously (for -1 Force each); reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: For important Imperial dignitaries, an individual Star Destroyer is placed at their personal disposal.
name: Alert My Star Destroyer! (V)

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Deploys -1 to \ul Finalizer\ul0 . While piloting \ul Finalizer\ul0 , it is immune to attrition < 8 (< 10 while with a Resistance character or [Resistance] starship). May be targeted by Imperial Command as if an admiral (even if a unit of Force).
lore: \b Leader.\b0
name: Captain Peavey

gametext: Deploy on Vader. While on Vader, may not be stolen and he is power +1. Instead of firing, may cancel the immunity to attrition of a Jedi present. May target a character for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny < defense value.
lore: Vader's lightsaber. Symbol of the most feared man in the galaxy. Vader's control of the dark side of the Force allows him to wield this weapon in surprising ways.
name: Darth Vader's Lightsaber (V)

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. You may initiate battles here for free. Once per turn, may cancel game text of opponent's character of ability < 4 at same site until end of turn. Immune to Clash Of Sabers, Sorry About The Mess, and attrition < 6.
lore: \b Leader.\b0
name: Darth Vader, Emperor's Enforcer

dark_side_text: Krennic deploys free here. Opponent may not limit Force generation at Death Star locations.
gametext: If a system was just 'blown away' by Superlaser, you lose 3 Force.\par Krennic deploys free here. Opponent may not limit Force generation at Death Star locations.
light_side_text: If a system was just 'blown away' by Superlaser, you lose 3 Force.
name: Death Star: War Room (V)

gametext: USED: Take 4-LOM, non-[Maintenance] Boba Fett, Danz Borin, or Dengar into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. LOST: During your move phase, your bounty hunter (or [Independent] starship they are piloting) may make an additional move. OR Move your bounty hunter as a 'react.'
lore: Having lost sight of Boba Fett, Luke was surprised by his sudden reappearance.
name: Double Back (V)

gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on table. While present with a Jedi, destroyer droids are defense value +2. If your destroyer droid was just lost, may stack it here. During your control phase, may use 2 Force to place any destroyer droid here in Used Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The Trade Federation utilizes such efficient methods of droid deployment that it is rumored even they do not know exactly how many battle droids are in circulation.
name: Droid Racks (V)

gametext: During battle with a stormtrooper, may cancel one just drawn automated or lightsaber weapon destiny. Permanent weapon is Z6 Riot Control Baton (may target a character for free; draw destiny; target hit if destiny > defense value).
lore: Stormtrooper.
name: FN-2199 (Nines)

dark_side_text: Once per game, may exchange an Interrupt from hand with bottom card of your Reserve Deck.
gametext: Ice Storm is canceled at Hoth sites.\par Once per game, may exchange an Interrupt from hand with bottom card of your Reserve Deck.
light_side_text: Ice Storm is canceled at Hoth sites.
name: Hoth: Ice Plains (V)

gametext: \ul Deploy Tuanul Village, any other [Episode VII] location, and I Will Finish What You Started. Opponent may reveal a unique (*) Resistance character from Reserve Deck; that card is a Resistance Agent. Otherwise, Luke is a Resistance Agent and loses immunity to attrition. \ul0 \par \b For\b0  remainder of game, non-[Episode VII] Dark Jedi are lost and Resistance Agents are immune to Set For Stun. \par \b Flip\b0  this card if your First Order characters control two battlegrounds and a Resistance Agent is not present at a battleground site.\par \b While\b0 this side up, where you have a First Order leader, opponent must first use or lose 1 Force to draw a card for battle destiny. Unless BB-8 on table, opponent's Force retrieval is canceled. If Kylo on table: During your turn, may stack an Interrupt from your Lost Pile face up on I Will Finish What You Started; and once per turn, may play an Interrupt stacked there as if from hand (then place that card out of play).\par \b Flip\b0  this card if you do not occupy two battlegrounds or if a Resistance Agent is present at a battleground site.
name: I Want That Map/And Now You'll Give It To Me

gametext: Deploy on table. Vader is lost. Once per turn, may stack an Interrupt from hand face up here to cancel a just drawn weapon destiny at Kylo's site. Kylo is power +1 for each card here. Once per game, may deploy a lightsaber from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
name: I Will Finish What You Started

dark_side_text: While you control, your superlaser weapon destiny draws are +1.
gametext: Unless Baze, Bodhi, Chirrut, or Saw here, Force drain -1 here.\par While you control, your superlaser weapon destiny draws are +1.
light_side_text: Unless Baze, Bodhi, Chirrut, or Saw here, Force drain -1 here.
name: Jedha

gametext: When deployed, may take a Royal Guard into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If in battle with an Imperial, once per game may cancel a non-[Immune To Sense] interrupt.
lore: Fiercely devoted Royal Guard. Feels deeply indebted to those who risk their life for him. Unaware of the extent of Palpatine's attrocities and cruelty.
name: Kir Kanos (V)

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. \ul When drawn for destiny, use 1 Force or this card is lost\ul0 . During your deploy phase, may use 3 Force to relocate Kylo from here to same site as a Resistance character,
name: Lieutenant Dopheld Mitaka

gametext: During battle with a Jedi (unless Obi-Wan here), your battle and weapon destiny draws are +1. Permanent weapon is (*)Maul's Lightsaber (may target a character for free; draw two destiny; target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value).
lore: Trade Federation.
name: Lord Maul With Lightsaber

gametext: Once per game, may take Always Two There Are or a Neimoidian into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If alone (or a [Theed Palace] objective on table) and opponent just initiated battle here, may exclude one character of ability < 6 present. Immune to attrition.
lore: \b Leader.\b0 Trade Federation.
name: Lord Sidious

gametext: May add 1 pilot and 2 passengers. Permanent pilot is (*)Mara Jade, who provides ability of 5. While alone and piloted by an Imperial, adds one battle destiny. Immune to attrition < 4.
name: Mara Jade In VT-49 Decimator

gametext: When deployed, may play a Defensive Shield from under your Starting Effect (as if from hand). While at opponent's battleground, Force drains here may not be reduced. Once per game, may use 1 Force to play opponent's just-played Interrupt out of play.
lore: Royal Guard \b leader\b0 . Remembers nothing of his past other than serving his Emperor. Early instructor of Kir Kanos and Carnor Jax.
name: Myn Kyneugh (V)

gametext: USED: Use 1 Force to deploy Krennic or a Jedha location from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. STARTING: Is Death Star on table, deploy Superlaser and up to two Effects that deploy on table and are always immune to Alter. Place this Interrupt in hand.
lore: "We shall double our efforts."
name: Operational As Planned (V)

gametext: USED: Take Downtown Plaza or a prison into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. LOST: Take one unique (*) bounty into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Target an alien. For remainder of turn, target is power and forfeit -1 (-3 if Chewie).
lore: Oouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouioouiooui-
name: Sonic Bombardment (V)

dark_side_text: Opponent may not limit Force generation at Starkiller Base locations. Once per turn, may deploy a Starkiller Base battleground from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
gametext: Opponent may not limit Force generation at Starkiller Base locations. Once per turn, may deploy a Starkiller Base battleground from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Starkiller Base

dark_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force (free if a First Order character present).
gametext: Your docking bay transit from here requires 3 Force.\par Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force (free if a First Order character present).
light_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 3 Force.
name: Starkiller Base: Docking Bay

dark_side_text: While Kylo armed with a lightsaber here, he is power +2.
gametext: While Rey armed with a lightsaber here, she is power +2.\par While Kylo armed with a lightsaber here, he is power +2.
light_side_text: While Rey armed with a lightsaber here, she is power +2.
name: Starkiller Base: Forest

dark_side_text: During your move phase, may use 2 Force to move Kylo between here and a battleground.
gametext: If Kylo here and Now You'll Give It To Me on table, opponent's Force drains are +2 here.\par During your move phase, may use 2 Force to move Kylo between here and a battleground.
light_side_text: If Kylo here and Now You'll Give It To Me on table, opponent's Force drains are +2 here.
name: Starkiller Base: Interrogation Room (Prison)

dark_side_text: If you control with a First Order leader, Force drain +1 here.
gametext: Chewie, Finn, and Han are deploy -1 and power +1 here.\par If you control with a First Order leader, Force drain +1 here.
light_side_text: Chewie, Finn, and Han are deploy -1 and power +1 here.
name: Starkiller Base: Shield Control

gametext: Deploy on an Imperial leader (may immediately take any one card into hand from Force Pile; reshuffle). Leia may not cancel Force drains where you have an Imperial. If on Tarkin, once per turn may peek at top card of any Reserve Deck.
lore: "You don't know how hard I found it signing the order to terminate your life."
name: Tarkin's Bounty (V)

dark_side_text: Your characters here and at Watto's Junkyard are immune to opponent's Sandwhirl.
gametext: For remainder of game, sites may not deploy between this site and Watto's Junkyard.\par Your characters here and at Watto's Junkyard are immune to opponent's Sandwhirl.
light_side_text: For remainder of game, sites may not deploy between this site and Watto's Junkyard.
name: Tatooine: Mos Espa (V)

gametext: Deploy on table. Non-unique destroyer droids are deploy -1 and forfeit +1. While all your characters at sites are destroyer droids and Neimoidians, opponent's characters are defense value -1 (to a minimum of 3) for each destroyer droid present. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: When two Jedi are attempting to breach your bridge, even a destroyer droid's response time seems far too slow.
name: Where Are Those Droidekas?! (V)

gametext: USED: Use 1 Force to [Upload] a [First Order] shuttle. STARTING: Deploy Jakku: Landing Site, Bow To The First Order, and one Effect that deploys on table and is always immune to Alter. Place this Interrupt in hand.
name: You Know What I've Come For

gametext: Place opponent's just drawn destiny on top of their Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR If opponent just lost Force from your [Episode I] objective, take any one card from Used Pile into hand; reshuffle.
lore: Needless to say, Watto was not happy about his loss.
name: You Swindled Me! (V)
